def: A genus of trees growing naturally on the Andes in Peru andadjacent countries, but now cultivated in the East Indies, producinga medicinal bark of great value.
The American golden plover. [Local, U. S.]
An aquatic plant (Hottonia palustris), having finely dividedleaves.
Not looked for; unexpected; as, an unlooked-for event.
An idol; a puppet; a doll. [Obs.] Selden. Shak.
A dainty morsel; a Welsh rabbit. See Welsh rabbit, underRabbit.
